David Ornstein on Arsenal: &ldquo;There&rsquo;s no real excuse now, it is all on the Kroenke&rsquo;s shoulders &amp; I think Josh has recognised that. I think he&rsquo;s going to be a more visible &amp; a regular presence around Arsenal now.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Ornstein on J Kroenke: &ldquo;He was very careful not to criticise past personal or regimes, especially Ars&egrave;ne Wenger, but he explained when Wenger was at the club, he would just hold a meeting with him, just the two of them making decisions. The all powerful traditional manager.&rdquo;

